description._content: Photographer: Unknown, Non-Indian Subject: George Gustav Heye (GGH), Non-Indian, 1874-1957 Date Created: 1918 Catalog Number: P11802 Format: Albumen print Dimensions: 3.25 x 4 in. Collection History: Between 1917 and 1923, the MAI mounted the Hendricks-Hodge Expedition to explore and excavate the historic Zuni village of Hawikku, one of the most extensive projects of its kind in the Southwest. Documentation of MAI expeditions and excavations often includes photographs of camp life and expedition members. Description: George Gustav Heye posed standing in an excavation pit Place: Hawikku (Hawikuh) Pueblo ruins; Zuni Reservation; Cibola County; New Mexico; USA Site Name: Hawikku (Hawikuh) Pueblo ruins Culture/People: A:shiwi (Zuni) (archaeological),Non-Indian Culture Hierarchy: Pueblo>A:shiwi (Zuni) (archaeological) Persistent URL:http://www.americanindian.si.edu/searchcollections/item.aspx?irn=313974 Repository:National Museum of the American Indian View more collections from the Smithsonian Institution.
